org.jcvi.jillion.assembly.consed.phd

Interface PhdReadTagVisitor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractPhdReadTagVisitor

    public interface PhdReadTagVisitor
    PhdReadTagVisitor is a Visitor that will visit a single PhdReadTag.
    Author:
    dkatzel
    See Also:
    PhdReadTag

    • Method Detail

      • visitType

        void visitType(String type)
        Visit the type of this tag.
        Parameters:
        type - a String describing the type, will never be null, but may be empty.

      • visitSource

        void visitSource(String source)
        Visit the source that generated this tag (usually the program name).
        Parameters:
        source - a String describing the source, will never be null, but may be empty.

      • visitUngappedRange

        void visitUngappedRange(Range ungappedRange)
        Visit the ungapped Range into the read that this tag refers.
        Parameters:
        ungappedRange - a Range; will never be null.

      • visitDate

        void visitDate(Date date)
        Visit the Date that this tag was created.
        Parameters:
        date - a Date; will never be null.

      • visitComment

        void visitComment(String comment)
        Visit the comment that goes along with this tag. If a tag does not have a comment, then this method will not be visited.
        Parameters:
        comment - a String; will never be null; but may be multi-line.

      • visitFreeFormData

        void visitFreeFormData(String data)
        Visit the comment that goes along with this tag. If a tag does not have any free form data, then this method will not be visited.
        Parameters:
        data - a String; will never be null; but may be multi-line.

      • visitEnd

        void visitEnd()
        The phd file has been completely visited.

      • halted

        void halted()
        The phd visitation has been halted, usually by calling PhdBallVisitorCallback.haltParsing().
